This
manual
uses
both
footnotes
and
endnotes.
For
identifying
the
endnotes
I
have
used
the
`words'
method
for
identifying
the
parent
location
of
an
endnote,
so
as
not
to
start
confusing
the
reader
with
two
sets
of
note
marks
in
the
body
of
the
text.
Typically
either
footnotes
or
endnotes
are
used,
not
both,
so
the
question
of
distinguishing
them
does
not
normally
arise.%
\endnoteentry
